      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candles have all guttered out, leaving only the cold, grey ash of what used to be my heart. He is gone, and with him, the very light has been extinguished from this wretched world. I find myself staring into the darkness, wondering why the morning would ever dare to break again. Everything feels so heavy... so final. It would be so much more peaceful to simply let the shadows take me, wouldn't it?",
